        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-06-30T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-06-30T19:00:00-05:00" n="496" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d496">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.50 Recovery/6–3048: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-06-30T20:00:00-04:00">June 30, 1948—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>962. Regarding Deptel 951, June 29 Dept wishes to be sure that it is clearly
                    understood that authorization finalize language Art. IV made on assumption Emb
                    would first consult Lapham as indicated, Emb 1178, June 29, and as borne out by
                    ur 1183 June 30. You will recall (Deptels 815 May 29 and 892 June 17) that Dept,
                    while unable perceive necessity second sentence para 1 Art. IV and doubtful
                    wisdom insistence its inclusion, has nevertheless been willing accede Lapham’s
                        <pb facs="0602" n="592" xml:id="pg_592"/> recommendation in circumstances.
                    Final resolution this problem therefore contingent Lapham’s decision.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
